        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(flock): bind allow-always to wrapped command",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nHardens exec approval binding for Linux `flock` wrapper usage by resolving supported file-plus-argv wrapper forms to the wrapped executable before durable allow-always patterns are stored or matched.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add conservative `flock` dispatch-wrapper parsing for `flock [options] file|directory command [arguments]`.\n- Fail closed for ambiguous command-string, fd-only, unlock, and unsupported option forms.\n- Cover documented option aliases including `-F`, `-o`, `--close`, `--nb`, `--no-fork`, `--wait`, and clustered flag usage such as `-en`.\n- Update user-facing exec approval wrapper lists to include `flock`.\n- Add regression coverage for wrapper resolution and allow-always bypass prevention.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/exec-wrapper-resolution.test.ts src/infra/exec-approvals-allow-always.test.ts`\n  - wrapper resolution: 132 passed\n  - allow-always approvals: 45 passed\n- `corepack pnpm docs:list`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main`\n  - clean: no accepted/actionable findings\n\nReal behavior proof:\n\n```text\n$ command -v flock\n/usr/bin/flock\n$ flock /tmp/openclaw-flock-proof.lock sh -c 'printf proof > \"$proof_file\"'\n$ cat \"$proof_file\"\nproof\n```\n\nApproval-analysis proof after the patch:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"persisted\": [\"benign-maintenance\"],\n  \"allowlistSatisfied\": false,\n  \"requiresApproval\": true\n}\n```\n\nThis shows an allow-always decision for `flock lockfile benign-maintenance` binds to the wrapped executable, and a later `flock lockfile payload` does not reuse that approval.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Existing allowlist entries that trusted the `flock` wrapper path may require a fresh approval for the wrapped executable after this hardening.\n",
